Tran Dinh Quang Vinh is a Junior AI Developer specialized in designing and implementing artificial intelligence and machine learning solutions, with a strong focus on Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computer Vision. Their core expertise lies in architectures such as LSTM, Transformer, and GPT, using frameworks like PyTorch, TensorFlow, and Hugging Face, to develop sequence-to-sequence models, language models, and face recognition systems. With a background in academic projects, Vinh has gained experience in collecting and preprocessing large datasets, implementing attention mechanisms, and optimizing hyperparameters using techniques like Reinforcement Learning (RL) with Proximal Policy Optimization (PPO) and Direct Preference Optimization (DPO). Notably, they have worked on projects involving machine translation, medical chatbots, fake news classification, and face recognition, demonstrating their ability to apply deep learning concepts to real-world problems.

Technically, Vinh is proficient in programming languages such as Python, Java, C, JavaScript, HTML, and CSS, and has hands-on experience with frameworks and libraries like OpenCV, Scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy, and Matplotlib. They are familiar with databases like SQL and Microsoft SQL Server, and have used cloud platforms like Google Drive for data storage and management. Additionally, Vinh has experience with DevOps tools like Git, GitHub, and Postman, and has worked with architectures like Seq2Seq, Doc2Vec, and Large Language Models (LLMs). Their domain knowledge spans NLP, Computer Vision, and Big Data, with a strong understanding of techniques like Data Preprocessing, Text Classification, Face Encoding, and Hyperparameter Optimization. With a solid foundation in data structures, algorithms, and object-oriented programming (OOP), Vinh is well-equipped to tackle complex AI and machine learning challenges, and is committed to continuous learning and professional growth.